I love this place. Pretty much anytime I'm working in the neighborhood I pop by for breakfast or lunch. No complaints on the bagels, accompaniments, portions, or price.  My go-to lunch is the Bird Sandwich which comes with turkey, Muenster cheese, lettuce, tomato and mayo. I like to get it on a toasted California bagel (I think they invented this type of bagel; it basically has a bunch of grains and oats in it and is a tinge sweet). All the sandwiches come with a bag of chips and a pickle, so it's quite a satisfying meal!  I'm also a big fan of their lox + plain cream cheese, which I like to enjoy sandwiched between a toasted sesame bagel.  They have like 15 other varieties of bagels and cream cheese, so whatever you fancy they probably have it.  If you're not in the mood for a bagel, you can also get sandwiches on sliced bread or rolls. You can even do a salad. They also have an impressive display of baked goods, packaged treats, and beverages for your snacking pleasure.  It can get a little busy during the breakfast and lunch rush, but the guys are fast so don't let the lines intimidate you.
